The paper discusses the use of Neural Networks (NNs) for power grid stability control, which falls under the category of control engineering. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning (RL) and Supervised Learning (SL) algorithms, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (AI) applications, making cs.AI the second most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the design and implementation methodologies of NNs, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (ML), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of NNs for renewable energy management and control, which falls under the category of Computational Engineering, making cs.NE (Numerical Analysis) the fourth most likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the works of researchers in the field of conventional and renewable energy systems, which falls under the category of Computer Engineering, making cs.CE (Computers and Society) the fifth most likely sub-category.
